<br>
You post is very good but I think you really miss why Verant does the things they do. Druids are to offensively geared now to see any drastic improvements in there healing ability. I do think they should be better at healing but not in the current form the druid class is in. They have far to much offense to be remotely close in healing compared to the cleric that has little.<br>
<br>
In your post you state how no druid/shaman can heal a group in endgame encounters so you must have a cleric. Well this is true to a large degree but look at topor, group regen, and 75% slow. Should a shaman be remotely close to a cleric in healing power given there offensive and defensive ability? I have to say no.<br>
<br>
Verant stated many times during the last class balancing over a year ago that druids and shamans are not meant to replace clerics, but a shaman and druid combined in a &quot;normal experience encounter&quot; should be able to keep things going fine in a group. Well a large portion of the game is normal exp'ing and in that area druid+shaman is greater then clerics at the post 51 lvls.  I don't think everyone has to be great in all areas of the game. I remember feeling very crappy in sol b pre-lvl 44. I also remember how much it sucked at lvl 56 not to have a magic based nuke higher then my lvl 44 spell. <br>
<br>
There are alot of areas of the game where everyone is just not going to be as affective as they would be under other conditions. IMO druids are damage dealers first and healers secondary. Look at the druids spell list, most of there spells are of a offensive or defensive nature. Shaman are buffers first and debuffers second and healing third.  It is to late to change CH now because not only have encounters been balanced around it but also the healing classes have been balanced around it. Complete heal has made it possible for druids to have nukes like Moonfire and for shaman to have 75% slow, topor, insane poison dots and Can4. Those classes have far more versatility then clerics. They have been geared away from healing and do other things far better. The cleric is only good at one thing and that is healing. Do to mob and weapon inflation clerics are sad against undead now. No one gets a cleric in a undead zone to be a offensive force like they did in the old days pre-kunark.<br>
<br>
Complete heal is overpowered and the other two healing classes in the game can't compete with that spell....BUT...those classes have things that make them viable at end game encounters. You need backup healers, slowers, debuffers, damage dealers in the endgame. Druids can be healer, debuffer, or damage dealer, and shamans can be slowers and debuffers but clerics can only be one thing really and there lies the balance no matter how screwed up it might be.<br>
<br>
